com.redhat.rhn.domain

Class Label

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.redhat.rhn.domain.Label
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    VirtualInstanceState, VirtualInstanceType

    public abstract class Label
extends java.lang.Object
    A Label is essentially a constant because Label implementations are mapped to read-only, reference tables where the Label objects/rows already exist. Reference tables like these consist of (at least) the following columns:
    • ID
    • NAME
    • LABEL
    • CREATED
    • MODIFIED
    Examples of these types of tables include rhnServerGroupType and rhnVirtualInstanceType. Additional columns can be mapped in subclasses.

    AbstractLabelNameHelper is conceptually the same as this class; however, it is not implemented as an immutable like this class.

    For an example of how to implement a Label, take a look at VirtualInstanceType and VirtualInstanceTypeFactory.
    See Also:
    VirtualInstanceType
